Salmon with Dill

4, salmon fillet
1/2 tsp, salt
1 tsp, pepper
2 tsp, onion powder
2 tsp, dried dill
4 tbsp, butter

30 minutes, serves 4

Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).

Rinse salmon and arrange baking dish, optionally wrapped in foil and parchment paper.

Sprinkle salt, pepper, onion powder, and dill over the fish. Place pieces of butter evenly over the fish.

Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Salmon is done when it flakes easily with a fork.

